news.title: Poland's Budimex reports 4% drop in net profit to $30.3 million in Q1 2025
news.para: Budimex is one of the certified partners of military investments in Poland. The company said in March that it wanted to actively participate in the country's military investments.

news.title: Lucknow civic body allocates ₹500 crore for infrastructure and smart city development
news.para: The decision to allocate funds for various development projects in the city was taken on Wednesday during a standing committee meeting chaired by Mayor Sushma Kharkwal at the Smart City office.

news.title: Higher interest rates to delay U.S. residential market recovery: CRH CEO
news.para: "The much needed recovery in U.S. residential is going to I think inevitably get pushed out," Jim Mintern told reporters after the company's annual general meeting.

news.title: India may need 50 million sq ft real estate, 45 TWH power for AI data centres by 2030: Report
news.para: As per Deloitte India's latest report, the country could require an additional 45-50 million square feet of real estate space and 40-45 Terawatt Hours (TWH) incremental power by 2030 to meet the growing demand for AI.

news.title: Star Housing Finance's profit rises 25% in FY25
news.para: For the twelve months ending March 31, 2025, Star HFL posted total revenue of Rs. 94.96 crs, a 54.06% y-o-y increase. Profit after tax (PAT) rose by 25% to Rs. 11.10 crs, compared to Rs. 8.88 crs in FY2023-24

news.title: MahaRERA crosses 50,000 housing project registrations
news.para: Tamil Nadu ranks second with 27,609 projects, followed by Gujarat with 15,322. These three states are the only ones in the country with over 10,000 registered housing developments.

news.title: Delhi: SC orders DDA to demolish illegal structures in Okhla village
news.para: The top court observed of the total 3 bighas and 8 biswas, which was not handed over to DDA, an area of 1 bigha and 8 biswas fell inside the boundary covered by PM-UDAY scheme and the remaining was outside the scheme's purview.

news.title: Asian Paints' profit falls 45% in Q4 FY25
news.para: Asian Paints, India's biggest paintmaker by market share, also incurred a one-time expense of 1.83 billion rupees, which includes losses from the sale of its operations in Indonesia.

news.title: Property Share files ₹472 crore IPO draft for second SM REIT scheme
news.para: PropShare Titania comprises a 4,37,973 sq ft of grade A+ office space in G Corp Tech Park located in Mumbai, with ESG certifications.

news.title: ED attaches ₹2,348 crore assets in money laundering case of WTC group
news.para: The action has been taken in "a massive real estate fraud involving WTC Faridabad Infrastructure Private Limited and other entities of the WTC Group, headed by Ashish Bhalla", the Enforcement Directorate (ED) said.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT's net operating income up 16% to ₹488.5 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: The company announced the distribution of Rs 319.1 crore (Rs. 5.25 per unit) to its unitholders for the March quarter, 10.5 per cent higher than the fourth quarter of the 2023-24 fiscal, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Maharashtra government approves conversion of 2.1 lakh sq metres of leasehold land into ownership for Maha Metro
news.para: A senior state government official said the land, previously leased to Maha Metro for 30 years, will now be transferred without conditions on an ownership basis.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government acquires 13,500 acres of land for new industrial city under BIDA
news.para: The official said the industrial city in Bundelkhand was an effort by the govt to strengthen region's economic foundations.

news.title: Compensation for land acquisition must be guided by equality, equity, justice: SC
news.para: The bench observed the acquisition proceedings commenced in April 2008 and the public purpose of the acquisition was to build Chaudhary Devi Lal Industrial Model Township.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC issues notices to state government on land allotment to LuLu Group
news.para: In another PIL filed by YSRCP MLA Lella Appi Reddy, challenging the issuance of NCDs to raise funds, the high court observed that it is a policy decision of the govt.

news.title: Jharkhand HC orders state government to mention timeframe for land survey
news.para: The court was hearing a PIL filed by Gokul Chand. Land survey had started in 1975, prior to bifurcation of the state.

news.title: TCS leases over one million sq ft of office space in Hyderabad
news.para: The lease spans all 19 floors of the building, from ground to the 18th floor, at a monthly rent of Rs 43 per sq. ft., totalling around Rs 4.37 crore per month.

news.title: Kolkata civic body bans future constructions on terraces and basements: Mayor
news.para: KMC consulted the civic legal department on the issue after four rooftop restaurants and lounge bars filed two separate petitions in Calcutta High Court.

news.title: Noida authority plans drone survey to tackle illegal constructions on floodplains
news.para: At a meeting chaired by Noida Authority CEO Lokesh M, a slew of measures was announced to tackle illegal farmhouses and unauthorised constructions mushrooming in the Hindon-Yamuna floodplains.

news.title: Sebi revises REIT, InvIT disclosure guidelines for offer documents
news.para: Sebi also specified additional disclosures, which will be included as a part of the audited financial information and shall also be subjected to audit.
